<item>
            <title>[FLINK-20081] ExecutorNotifier should run handler in the main thread when receive an exception from the callable.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-20081</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the &lt;tt&gt;ExecutorNotifier&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;runs the &lt;tt&gt;handler&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;in the worker thread if there is an exception thrown from the &lt;tt&gt;callable&lt;/tt&gt;. This breaks the threading model and prevents an exception from bubbling up to fail the job.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another issue is that right now, when an exception bubbles up from the &lt;tt&gt;SourceCoordinator&lt;/tt&gt;, the UncaughtExceptionHandler will call System.exit(-17) and kill the JM. This is too much. Instead, we should just fail the job to trigger a failover.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
